      <pubDate>Mon, 30 May 2016 12:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://oliviergimenez.github.io/blog/polar_bear/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;My post-doc Sarah Cubaynes and I went to visit our colleague
&lt;a href=&#34;http://www.npolar.no/en/people/jon.aars/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Jon Aars&lt;/a&gt; in
Tromso, Norway. We are working together on the demography of polar bears using an amazing dataset
the &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.npolar.no/en/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Norwegian Polar Institute&lt;/a&gt; has
been collecting for decades. It was also the opportunity to catch up with
&lt;a href=&#34;https://uit.no/om/enhet/ansatte/person?p_document_id=41160&amp;p_dimension_id=88165&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Nigel (Gilles)
Yoccoz&lt;/a&gt; who&amp;rsquo;s being very helpful with this project. Jon took us fishing; I was luckier than with fly-fishing ;-)&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
